        <!-- How to Calculate GPA -->
        <div id="gpaCalculation" class="mt-4">
            <h4 class="text-success">ðŸ“Œ How to Calculate GPA</h4>
            <p>GPA (Grade Point Average) is calculated by dividing the total grade points earned by the total credit units taken in a semester.</p>
            <h5 class="text-primary">Formula:</h5>
            <p><b>GPA = Total Grade Points / Total Credit Units</b></p>
            <h5 class="text-primary">Example Calculation:</h5>
            <table class="table table-bordered">
                <thead class="">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Course</th>
                        <th>Credit Unit</th>
                        <th>Grade</th>
                        <th>Grade Point</th>
                        <th>Total Points</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>MAT101</td>
                        <td>3</td>
                        <td>A</td>
                        <td>5</td>
                        <td>15</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>PHY102</td>
                        <td>2</td>
                        <td>B</td>
                        <td>4</td>
                        <td>8</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CHM103</td>
                        <td>3</td>
                        <td>C</td>
                        <td>3</td>
                        <td>9</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="table-info">
                        <td><b>Total</b></td>
                        <td><b>8</b></td>
                        <td></td>
                        <td></td>
                        <td><b>32</b></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><b>GPA = 32 Ã· 8 = 4.0</b></p>
        </div>

        <!-- How to Calculate CGPA -->
        <div id="cgpaCalculation" class="mt-4">
            <h4 class="text-success">ðŸ“Œ How to Calculate CGPA</h4>
            <p>CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) is the overall GPA from all semesters.</p>
            <h5 class="text-primary">Formula:</h5>
            <p><b>CGPA = Total Grade Points Earned in All Semesters / Total Credit Units Taken</b></p>
            <h5 class="text-primary">Example Calculation:</h5>
            <table class="table table-bordered" border="2">
                <thead class="table-dark">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Semester</th>
                        <th>Total Credit Units</th>
                        <th>Total Grade Points</th>
                        <th>GPA</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>First Semester</td>
                        <td>18</td>
                        <td>72</td>
                        <td>4.0</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Second Semester</td>
                        <td>20</td>
                        <td>76</td>
                        <td>3.8</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="table-info">
                        <td><b>Total</b></td>
                        <td><b>38</b></td>
                        <td><b>148</b></td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><b>CGPA = 148 Ã· 38 = 3.89</b></p>
        </div>

        <!-- UNN Grading System -->
        <div id="gradingSystem" class="mt-4">
            <h4 class="text-success">ðŸ“Œ Nigeria Universities Grading System</h4>
